  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 390°F/ Gas 6</p><p>Put a large baking tray in the oven to heat up (this will stop the pizza bottoms from going soggy!)</p><p>Remove the <strong>sausage meat</strong> from their<strong> </strong>skins and discard the skins</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid), with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sausage meat</strong>, breaking it up into small pieces with a wooden spoon as you go, then add the <strong>fennel seeds</strong> (not a fan of aniseed? Go easy!)</p><p>Cook for 4 min or until the<strong> </strong>sausage meat is brown and crispy</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the <strong>tomato paste</strong>, a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong>, a splash of <strong>cold water</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> in a small bowl</p><p>Season generously with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>- this is your<strong> tomato sauce</strong></p><p>Drain the <strong>mozzarella</strong>, tear it into bite-sized pieces, and pat it dry with <strong>kitchen paper</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the heated baking tray from the oven and add the<strong> pizza bases</strong></p><p>Spread the <strong>tomato sauce</strong> over the<strong> pizza bases </strong>with the back of a spoon</p><p>Dot the <strong>torn</strong> <strong>mozzarella</strong> over and put the tray in the oven until step 6</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the pizza bases are in the oven, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>baby kale</strong> to the pan with the sausage meat</p><p>Cook, covered for 1-2 min or until the <strong>baby</strong> <strong>kale</strong> is starting to wilt - this is your <strong>kale & sausage mixture</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the kale has wilted, top the<strong> pizza bases</strong> with the<strong> kale & sausage mixture</strong></p><p>Return them to the oven for 10-12 min or until the mozzarella<strong> </strong>has melted and the pizza bases are crispy - these are your <strong>fennel, sausage & baby kale pizzas</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Chop the <strong>basil leaves </strong>finely</p><p>Add both to a bowl and drizzle with <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a gentle mix up – this is your <strong>tomato & basil salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1077.-step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
